Cheers to being CUFFED and loving it here! 2023 is MY year, OUR year! I speak peace and prosperity over myself and my loved ones! Welcome to 2023, Tootie Girl!!! Do your best and give your best ✨️

It's a baby girl... 🎀 A few weeks before finding out I was pregnant with our Lil' Lovie, I cried hysterically in the shower about not ever being able to mother my own children. It was becoming reality after so many losses throughout the years that it would never happen and that maybe I didn't deserve for it to happen. The feeling was crushing. All babe could do was stand there getting wet while holding me, consoling me. BUT. I was already carrying my own tiny piece of God's love in human form. We were shocked. Like really shocked. There are truly no words to describe what ALL I feel, but I'm grateful. And so excited! I can't wait to see her little face, snuggle her close, smell her little neck, hear her laugh... watch her grow. I'm just... 🥹 Thank you, Lord, for our daughter!  Keep her safe and growing... keep us healthy and see us through to the end of a safe and uneventful entrance into this world.  AMEN. 🙏🏾✨️
.
.
.

23 pounds down since the positive test! Before becoming pregnant, I was on a fitness journey HEAVY. I think that has been my saving grace so far as to why I have been able to keep the major things at bay. No chronic high blood pressure, no gestational diabetes, no chronic edema. I've been eating right, drinking my water, going to yoga and pointe, doing low impact cardio and stretching to keep the cramps and ligament pain to a minimum. So far, so good. Cheers to the road to 5 months and erasing stereotypes and stigmatisms! And HAPPY GROWING, DOLL BABY! 🙌🏾 ✨️ ✨️✨️✨️

12 years ago today... I went into a surgery that changed my life forever. I literally was on my death bed when they put me under with a 20% chance of making it! Every now and then... I ask God why He kept me here. Why did He spare my life when I should have been dead and gone? Most do NOT survive sepsis of the blood like I encountered, let alone learning to live with one lung. But. It's because He had so much more in store for me. More life, more love and definitely more assignments to fulfill. I can't help but to marvel at God's timing, God's works and His unfailing love towards me.

Today on the 12th Anniversary of God pulling me through... I am staring at my daughter as she sleeps peacefully. The plan was for me to be her Mommy. 🥹 No matter what, she is my biggest blessing and my greatest and most meaningful accomplishment. 

I can't help but to think I was destined to be here. This day. This moment. 12 years later.

This is why. Eislyn is my why. 🫶🏾
.
.
.
